rComments: I dropped the course in the 4th week, very unrealistic and so much reading (as if we have only this class to study). Also, TA's seem not to follow his instructions. Overall, chaotic style, avoid if possible.

He uses questions twice a week, discussion posts, and 2 personal essays as a way to grade the class. No exams or midterms. A lot of people liked this format but it was definitely too much for me who was taking 6 classes that semester and working part-time. It's not hard to do well in this class but it does take diligence and time. Be prepared.

Professor Denis is a very good professor! For his class, there is no exam or midterms but there are weekly questions you have to answer and 2 personal essays to complete for the entire school year. The questions are graded out of 4 and most people usually get 3 or 3.5 out of 4 twice every week. Make sure to listen to the audio lectures and READ.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Very nice guy. I genuinely liked his content. Online structuring was very convenient and Claude was very adaptable. Zoom lectures were fun and he encouraged and was open minded for in class discussions. He was over all supportive and here for his students. You will get a good grade if you follow instructions. Effort is key!

I took this course online (because of COVID-19). He is one of the most organized professors I have had during these crazy times. This course made me remember why I like sociology, as the focus was on genuine learning over assignments.

Claude was a really good prof for this class, and teaches the material well. The quiz/midterm/exam were all straight forward, and there were no surprise questions on the tests. Be prepared for heavy lectures and a lot of reading since he posts no slides (all test material is based on readings and what was said in class). Not a class you can skip.

Honestly, if you can avoid him, do so. His lectures are soo boring and monotone. You do not need to show up to get a good grade. He tends to jump off-topic and confuse students throughout his lecture. If I could go back in time, I would drop out of his class. He makes sociology depressing and boring.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: I really enjoyed this class. We had a quiz, a midterm, an online discussion and a final. I found that the readings in the textbook were very difficult to follow but, his lectures cleared up a lot of my confusion. I would say that if you skipped his lectures and did not understand the readings your mark would definitely suffer accordingly.

As long as he sees an effort he will give in and help you out. If you can send him bare emails or meet with him ask questions before and after class, make him remember your name (because you always approach him for help) once he knows your name he will do his part to help you pass and you just gotta do yours.
Excellent Prof.

There is a lot of criticism from what I can see, but the Claude says it himself: he will not give an A unless you are an exceptional student. Don't take his classes if you are not passionate about Sociology or Pol Sci. Excellent professor - will be doing my master's under his supervision.
Knows what he's talking about but gets off topic so he doesn't get to all the material. Somewhat hard marker. Lots of tough reading for this particular class.

DON'T TAKE THIS COURSE! We didn't learn ANYTHING in the lectures, He spends his time talking about useless things and then quickly runs over the essential stuff. Had to figure out the material by myself using the book, which He never talks about, and the internet.

I loved this class. Denis teaches it really well; he's incredibly smart. This prof is a really nice guy but a little scatter brained, he tends to go off topic almost every class. Sometimes the material was confusing but I really enjoyed both the course and the teacher

Worst class ever. I dreaded going to this class because the way he teaches is extremely boring, but not the course itself. Anyway, watch out for this guy because he randomly pops final exam questions that make no sense and are mandatory. Not taking a class with him ever again!

Nice teacher, you can see that he's a smart guy. But his class has no structure what so ever ; he's all over the place, and it makes it hard to stay focus. Overall, a very nice guy, with a lack of direction when it comes to teaching his class.

You can tell he's a really smart guy and knows a lot about political science but the man does not know how to teach a class.
